1. Know how to create pages and folders. Appreciate the hierachy structure and be able to move them around. Know that these files and folders are saved in a dedicated folder that you open in Obisidian when you begin. 
2. Know that there is an edit mode (pen icon at the top right) and a preview mode. Click on the pen icon to see how the page is formatted.
3. Know how to format text. Look into the edit mode and see how **bold** and _underlining_ are done. 
4. Know how to create link to external website. This is a [website!](https://guides.github.com/features/mastering-markdown/) that shows you how to format the text (call markdown text).  
5. Know how to create back links. For example, you probably reach this page from [[2. Schedule]]
6. Know that these backlinks can be used to create a concept map using the _graph view_ at the left panel.
7. Know how to embede YouTube videos such as this:    
